						<p>On the east wall of the Kuraṅganātha temple.</p>						

						<p>Māṟavarmaṉ Vikramapāṇḍya.</p>						

						<p>This inscription contains portion of the <hi rend="italic">praśasti Tirumagaḷ Jayamagaḷ</hi> etc., of Māṟavarmaṉ Vikramapāṇḍya.</p>						

						<p>This mentions Śrī Rājarāja-chaturvēdi[maṅgalam]. Other details are lost as the inscription is fragmentary. </p>						

